### Test the Health Check Endpoint
GET http://localhost:3000/health

###

### Create a New Workout Session
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Push Day A"
}

###

### Test Validation (Should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}
### Fetch All Workouts (Should see an array of whatever you've created)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts

###

### Fetch a Specific Workout (REPLACE the ID below with a real ID generated from your POST test)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts/5rhn5nj

###

### Test 404 Handling with a fake ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts/non-existent-id-123

### Log a Set for a Workout (REPLACE the workout ID in the URL with your active workout ID)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts/5rhn5nj/sets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "exercise_name": "Bench Press",
  "weight": 100,
  "reps": 8,
  "rpe": 8.5
}

###

### Fetch the Workout Again to see the Joined Sets (REPLACE the workout ID in the URL)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/workouts/REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_ID